SIMPLE: observable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Observable
<hw>Ob*serv"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>observabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>observable</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of being observed; discernible;
noticeable.</def> <rj><au>Sir. T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The difference is sufficiently <qex>observable</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Southey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Worthy of being observed; important enough to be
noted or celebrated; <as>as, an <ex>observable</ex>
anniversary</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Noteworthy; remarkable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ob*serv"a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Ob*serv"a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Observance</ent>⟦br⟧
